{0 Meta-Theory}

{1 Soundness}

{!module-SpecV2.Soundness} proves that valid generated triples, together with
true user invariants on admissible executions, imply conditional safety.

{1 Relative Completeness}

{!module-SpecV2.RelativeCompleteness} proves the converse admissible-run
results:

- global correctness implies admissible validity of generated safety triples;
- under true invariants on admissible runs, global correctness implies
  admissible validity of all generated triples.
